@startuml
title 3. Submit for Review (Push + Create PR)
skinparam style strictuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam noteFontSize 11

actor Student as S
participant "GitWizard" as W
participant "Git" as G
participant "GitHub CLI" as GH
participant "GitHub" as R
actor Teammate as T

S -> W : Select option 3
W -> G : git branch --show-current
G --> W : feature/BR-02-edit-existing-community

W -> G : git status --porcelain
G --> W : (clean)

== Step 1: Push branch ==

W -> S : "Push branch to GitHub?\nProceed? (y/n)"
S -> W : y
W -> G : git push -u origin\nfeature/BR-02-edit-existing-community
G -> R : Upload commits
R --> G : Branch created on remote
G --> W : Push successful
W -> S : "Branch pushed."

== Step 2: Create Pull Request ==

W -> S : "PR title?"
S -> W : "Implement edit community (BR-02)"
W -> S : "PR: feature/BR-02-... -> main\nProceed?"
S -> W : y

W -> GH : gh pr create\n--base main\n--title "Implement edit community (BR-02)"\n--body "## Changes\n- ...\n## Checklist\n- [ ] Code compiles\n- [ ] Tests pass\n\nRelates to #2"
GH -> R : POST /repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls
R --> GH : PR #35 created
GH --> W : https://github.com/.../pull/35

W -> S : "Pull Request created!"

== After PR creation ==

note over S, T
  The wizard is done.
  Now the team collaboration begins.
end note

S -> T : "Please review PR #35"
T -> R : Review code changes
T -> R : Approve PR
R -> R : CI (GitHub Actions)\nruns and passes

note right of S
  Once approved and CI green,
  use option 4 to merge.
end note
@enduml
